heroDescription:
A three-sided marketplace: <strong>eaters</strong> order, <strong>merchants</strong> prepare, <strong>Dashers</strong> deliver. The hard parts:
      a <span class="hl">dispatch engine</span> that assigns the right Dasher to the right order in real-time optimizing for ETA, efficiency, and driver earnings; a <span class="hl-accent">live ETA system</span> updating predictions every few seconds based on traffic, restaurant prep time, and Dasher position;
      and a <span class="hl-accent">transactional order lifecycle</span> that doesn't lose your $47 burrito when the payment processor burps. DoorDash does ~2B orders/year; ~6M orders/day.
